    57	<objective>
    58	Wire a new `mzpeak` output format end-to-end through the TRFP CLI and emit the thinnest honest
    59	archive that the reference Python reader can OPEN: a STORED ZIP containing a ZSTD-internal Parquet
    60	facet pair (`spectra_data.parquet` + `spectra_metadata.parquet`) plus `mzpeak_index.json`, built
    61	from one real spectrum's points using the inherited `SpectrumWriter` data access. This retires the
    62	single biggest project unknown — that Parquet.Net 5.0.1's low-level API expresses mzPeak's nested
    63	column shapes — and lays the reusable PARAM/CV helpers Phase 3 depends on.
    64	
    65	Purpose: Prove the full pipeline before any fidelity is added; unblock Phases 2-4.
    66	Output: `OutputFormat.MzPeak`, help/dispatch/gzip/stream wiring, `MzPeakSpectrumWriter`, shared
    67	`MzPeakParquet` helper, and a reader-openable `<raw>.mzpeak`.
    68	</objective>
