    95	Parquet.Net 5.0.1 low-level surface (verified by spike, RESEARCH "verified API surface"):
    96	- new ParquetSchema(params Field[]);  schema.GetDataFields() -> DataField[] in leaf order
    97	- new StructField(string name, params Field[] elements)
    98	- new ListField(string name, Field item)
    99	- new DataField<T>(string name, bool? nullable = null)
   100	- new DataColumn(DataField field, Array data)
   101	- new DataColumn(DataField field, Array definedData, int[] definitionLevels, int[] repetitionLevels)
   102	- await ParquetWriter.CreateAsync(schema, stream)  -> ParquetWriter
   103	    .CompressionMethod = CompressionMethod.Zstd;  .CustomMetadata = IReadOnlyDictionary<string,string>;
   104	    .CreateRowGroup() -> ParquetRowGroupWriter;   rg.WriteColumnAsync(DataColumn)
   105	
   106	Parquet.Net path semantics (DO NOT string-split with '/'):
   107	- A DataField's identity is the leaf object returned by schema.GetDataFields(). Pair each returned
   108	  DataField with the caller-supplied array directly; never parse Path.ToString() with '/'.
   109	- DataField.Path is a FieldPath whose ToString() is DOT-separated (e.g. "spectrum.mz_range.lo"),
   110	  NOT '/'-separated. If a string key is ever needed, use the dot-separated FieldPath, but the write
   111	  helper keys on the DataField objects themselves.
   112	- DataColumn default codec is Snappy; ZSTD MUST be set explicitly on the writer and proven on read.
   113	
   114	Existing ctor analogs (all delegate to base, one arg):
   115	- ParquetSpectrumWriter(ParseInput) : base(parseInput)  // Writer/ParquetSpectrumWriter.cs:43
   116	</interfaces>
   117	</context>
   118	
   119	<constraints>
   120	- Parquet.Net LOW-LEVEL API only (ParquetSchema/DataColumn/ParquetWriter). NEVER ParquetSerializer.
   121	- m/z = float64, intensity = float32 (canonical widths).
   122	- ZIP = STORED (CompressionLevel.NoCompression). Parquet-internal codec = ZSTD (must be set; Parquet.Net
   123	  default is Snappy).
   124	- Plain string / list (32-bit offset) are accepted by the reader; do NOT chase large_string/large_list.
   125	- Build each Parquet facet fully in a MemoryStream (Parquet.Net needs a seekable stream + footer on dispose),
   126	  then write finished bytes into the STORED zip entry. Never hand Parquet.Net a non-seekable zip-entry stream.
   127	- Reuse inherited SpectrumWriter data access (ReadMZData, RetentionTimeFromScanNumber, MSOrder).
   128	  Do NOT re-decode Thermo data.
   129	- Code must be compact. ImplicitUsings is disabled — every `using` must be explicit. Keep files BOM-free.
   130	- NO comments referencing the harness, GSD, process, phases, or spikes anywhere in code.
