   201	    Accession, Unit, and String are NULLABLE reference fields per the PARAM schema; the value-struct
   202	    column-writer must emit null for them via definition levels when absent.
   203	    Implement, mirroring the verified pattern in RESEARCH:
   204	    - `public static StructField BuildParamField(string name)` -> the PARAM struct in the documented leaf
   205	      order (value/integer, value/float, value/string, value/boolean, accession, name, unit).
   206	    - `public static string CvColumn(string accession, string label, string unitAccession = null)` ->
   207	      convention `MS_<acc>_<label>[_unit_<NS>_<acc>]` with the `:` in CURIEs replaced by `_`
   208	      (e.g. MS:1000511 -> MS_1000511). CONTRACT: callers pass `label` already normalized to snake_case;
