   263	         ]}
   264	    2. `spectra_metadata.parquet` — schema with a top-level `spectrum` struct carrying at least an
   265	       `index:ulong` leaf (reader requires `spectrum.index`); include `id:string` and `time:double` for
   266	       honesty. One row, index 0. CustomMetadata: `spectrum_count` = "1", and the metadata-facet
   267	       `spectrum_data_point_count` = "0" (ground-truth convention — the real point count lives ONLY on
   268	       the data facet above; the OPEN gate confirms this is accepted).
   269	       (Both facets are REQUIRED for the reader OPEN — RESEARCH Unknown 4.)
   270	
   271	    Hand-build `mzpeak_index.json` with Newtonsoft.Json listing EXACTLY the two facets written:
   272	    `{"files":[{"name":"spectra_data.parquet","entity_type":"spectrum","data_kind":"data arrays"},
   273	    {"name":"spectra_metadata.parquet","entity_type":"spectrum","data_kind":"metadata"}],"metadata":{}}`.
   274	    Never list a facet you did not write.
   275	
   276	    Pack into a STORED zip layered on the configured output stream:
   277	    `using (var zip = new ZipArchive(Writer.BaseStream, ZipArchiveMode.Create, leaveOpen: true)) { ... }`,
   278	    creating each entry `zip.CreateEntry(name, CompressionLevel.NoCompression)` (STORED) and writing the
   279	    bytes: `mzpeak_index.json`, `spectra_data.parquet`, `spectra_metadata.parquet`. DISPOSE the
   280	    ZipArchive (exit the `using`) BEFORE `Writer.Flush(); Writer.Close();` so the zip central directory is
   281	    finalized while the base stream stays open (leaveOpen: true) for the writer to flush/close. Output
   282	    name is `<raw>.mzpeak` via ConfigureWriter. Add any low-level column-emit convenience to MzPeakParquet
   283	    if it keeps the writer compact.
   284	  </action>
   285	  <verify>
   286	    <automated>DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1 dotnet build -c Release ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.csproj 2>&1 | tail -3 | grep -qi "Build succeeded" && OUT=$(mktemp -d) && DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1 dotnet run -c Release --project ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.csproj -- -i ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/Data/small.RAW -b "$OUT" -f mzpeak 2>"$OUT/run.log"; RC=$?; test $RC -eq 0 && ! grep -qi "ERROR" "$OUT/run.log" && MZP=$(ls "$OUT"/*.mzpeak 2>/dev/null | head -1) && python3 -c "import zipfile,json; z=zipfile.ZipFile('$MZP'); assert all(i.compress_type==0 for i in z.infolist()); json.load(z.open('mzpeak_index.json')); print('STORED+INDEX OK')" && python3 -c "import pyarrow.parquet as pq, zipfile, io; z=zipfile.ZipFile('$MZP'); [exec('md=pq.read_metadata(io.BytesIO(z.read(n))); assert all(md.row_group(0).column(c).compression==\"ZSTD\" for c in range(md.row_group(0).num_columns)), n') for n in ('spectra_data.parquet','spectra_metadata.parquet')]; print('ZSTD OK')" && PYTHONPATH=refs/mzPeak/python python3.11 -c "import numpy, numpy.typing; from mzpeak import MzPeakFile; f=MzPeakFile('$MZP'); assert f.spectrum_metadata is not None and len(f.spectrum_metadata)>=1; print('OPEN OK', len(f.spectrum_metadata))"</automated>
   287	  </verify>
