   292	
   293	<build_runtime_setup>
   294	The csproj targets `net8.0`; this machine has the .NET 10 SDK (10.0.301) and the 9.0/10.0 runtimes but
   295	NOT the .NET 8 runtime. Resolve as follows:
   296	
   297	1. BUILD relies on NuGet auto-restore of the net8 reference/targeting pack
   298	   (`Microsoft.NETCore.App.Ref` 8.x), which the .NET 10 SDK pulls from NuGet automatically. Run a plain
   299	   `dotnet build -c Release ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParser.csproj` first.
   300	2. ONLY IF that restore/build fails with a missing net8 ref pack, install the .NET 8 SDK (which carries
   301	   the ref pack), then rebuild. Do not edit the csproj target framework.
   302	3. RUN/TEST (not build) is where roll-forward applies: the produced net8 assembly executes on the net9/10
   303	   runtime via `DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD=LatestMajor` + `DOTNET_ROLL_FORWARD_TO_PRERELEASE=1`. These env exports
   304	   are placed directly inside each verify command that runs `dotnet build`/`run`/`test` above; keep them
   305	   there. Parquet.Net 5.0.1's net8.0 lib loads cleanly under net9/10. Document the chosen approach in the
   306	   SUMMARY.
   307	4. Reference Python OPEN gate needs `python3.11` with `pyarrow`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `pynumpress`, `psims`.
   308	   Install the latter two if absent: `python3.11 -m pip install pynumpress psims`. Force `import numpy.typing`
   309	   before `from mzpeak import MzPeakFile` (older numpy build does not auto-load the typing submodule).
   310	</build_runtime_setup>
   311	
   312	<threat_model>
   313	## Trust Boundaries
   314	
   315	| Boundary | Description |
   316	|----------|-------------|
   317	| RAW file -> writer | Thermo RAW is parsed by trusted, already-shipping TRFP reader code (reused, not new) |
   318	| writer -> .mzpeak archive | New code constructs Parquet + zip bytes consumed by external readers |
   319	| .mzpeak -> reference reader | OPEN gate runs an external Python process over the produced file |
   320	
   321	## STRIDE Threat Register
   322	
   323	| Threat ID | Category | Component | Disposition | Mitigation Plan |
   324	|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
   325	| T-01-01 | Tampering | mzpeak_index.json lists a facet not actually written | mitigate | Emit JSON listing EXACTLY the two facets written; reader fails OPEN otherwise |
   326	| T-01-02 | Denial of Service | Zero-point spectrum -> empty/invalid facet | mitigate | Select the first in-range spectrum with >= 1 real point; if none, throw RawFileParserException and emit no archive (never fabricate a point) |
   327	| T-01-03 | Information Disclosure | Accidental deflate (CompressionLevel default) breaks STORED contract | mitigate | Force `CompressionLevel.NoCompression`; verify `compress_type==0` in the gate |
   328	| T-01-04 | Tampering | Parquet codec silently left at Snappy default, violating PQ-03 | mitigate | Set `CompressionMethod.Zstd`; gate reads both parquet entries' column-chunk metadata and asserts ZSTD |
   329	| T-01-SC | Tampering | npm/pip/cargo installs | accept | No new C# NuGet packages (Parquet.Net/Newtonsoft already deps). Only pip installs are `pynumpress`/`psims` into the local test env, verified on pypi.org during research; not shipped in output |
   330	</threat_model>
   331	
   332	<verification>
   333	- `dotnet build -c Release` succeeds via NuGet net8 ref-pack auto-restore (see build_runtime_setup).
   334	- `dotnet test --filter MzPeakParquet` green (PQ-01, PQ-02 round-trip + def/rep lock + nullable PARAM).
   335	- End-to-end run on `small.RAW` exits 0 with no ERROR line and produces `<raw>.mzpeak`; structural gate
   336	  (STORED + index) passes; both parquet facets assert ZSTD column-chunk compression; reference Python
   337	  OPEN gate exits 0 (PQ-03).
   338	- `parseInput.Errors == 0 && parseInput.Warnings == 0` on the clean small.RAW.
   339	</verification>
   340	
   341	<success_criteria>
   342	1. `-f mzpeak` / `-f 4` accepted, listed in MainClass and README --format help, output has `.mzpeak` extension. [CLI-01, CLI-02]
   343	2. Dispatch instantiates MzPeakSpectrumWriter; conversion completes without error (exit 0, no ERROR). [CLI-03]
   344	3. Parquet.Net low-level nested struct + list-of-struct + parallel nullable top-level columns round-trip
   345	   read confirms values; def/rep levels locked. [PQ-01]
   346	4. Reusable public PARAM value-struct builder + CV-accession column-name helper + Column helper exist in a
   347	   shared support file. [PQ-02]
   348	5. Archive is STORED ZIP with proven ZSTD-internal Parquet; reference Python reader OPENs it. [PQ-03]
   349	</success_criteria>
   350	
   351	<dependencies>
   352	- None upstream (first phase).
   353	- Build: NuGet auto-restore of `Microsoft.NETCore.App.Ref` 8.x (install .NET 8 SDK only if that fails).
   354	- Run/test: roll-forward env vars in the verify commands (see build_runtime_setup).
   355	- OPEN gate: python3.11 + pyarrow/pandas/numpy/pynumpress/psims; reference reader vendored at
   356	  `refs/mzPeak/python/`.
   357	- Test fixture: `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/Data/small.RAW`.
   358	- Reused C# deps (already in csproj): Parquet.Net 5.0.1, Newtonsoft.Json 13.0.3, System.IO.Compression.
   359	</dependencies>
   360	
   361	<risks>
   362	- Build runtime mismatch (net8 target vs net9/10 machine) — build via NuGet net8 ref-pack restore;
   363	  run/test via roll-forward env vars in the verify commands.
   364	- Reader OPEN requires BOTH `(spectrum, data arrays)` and `(spectrum, metadata)` facets with their KV keys
   365	  (`spectrum_count`, `spectrum_data_point_count`, `spectrum_array_index`, and a `spectrum.index` leaf) —
   366	  baked into Task 3; omission causes KeyError/IndexError in the reader.
   367	- Parquet codec default is Snappy — ZSTD must be set AND proven; the gate reads column-chunk metadata.
   368	- Column write order / nullable-array pitfalls in Parquet.Net — mitigated by pairing each leaf from
   369	  `GetDataFields()` with its array by DataField identity and passing defined-only values via the `Column`
   370	  helper with explicit definition levels (Task 2 helper).
   371	- No in-range spectrum with points — Task 3 throws RawFileParserException rather than fabricating.
   372	- OPEN gate environment drift (system python < 3.11) — gate pinned to `python3.11`; `numpy.typing` force-import.
   373	</risks>
